# PLATFORM Twilio credentials (ADR-009 Tier 0 — platform-billed sends only:
# tenant onboarding, environment registration, tenant-OWNER recovery,
# operator MFA). Tenant end-user sends NEVER use these; tenants supply their
# own via Connect or envelope-encrypted config in the tenant console.
#
# To populate (values are NOT committed in the clear):
#   cd deployment-configuration/profiles/dev/sesame-idam/idam/runtime
#   cp twilio.secrets.env.EXAMPLE twilio.secrets.env
#   $EDITOR twilio.secrets.env            # paste the real SID + token
#   sops -e -i twilio.secrets.env         # encrypts in place (.sops.yaml rule)
#   git add twilio.secrets.env            # ciphertext only
#
# Then set SMS_PROVIDER=twilio in the service env to leave mock mode.
TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID=ACxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN=your-auth-token-here
# Sender identity: a Messaging Service SID is preferred (number pools,
# compliance, geo-routing). Otherwise set TWILIO_FROM_NUMBER in E.164.
TWILIO_MESSAGING_SERVICE_SID=MGxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
# TWILIO_FROM_NUMBER=+15551234567
